stylometry: Trade off managers must consider when dealing with waiting lines is the time it takes a customer to go through the line and the costs of opening up another register and paying a worker.  Is an extra line worth the expense if a person waiting in line gets through in 5 minutes.  The objective is to minimize the number of lines which lowers cost and getting the customer through as quick as possible. Grocery stores and retail stores experience a higher number of customers than a bank or a fast food restaurant.  The respective company has to determine if it will improve the customers experince and raise the probability of them coming back if the wait in the line is less than what occured for them.
